Â Â Â Â http.authorizeRequests()
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â .antMatchers("/admin/**").hasRole("ADMIN")
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â .anyRequest().authenticated()
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â .and()
Â Â Â Â Â Â Â Â .formLogin();
}



14. What is the role of AuthenticationManager?
It handles the authentication process by verifying credentials and returning an AuthenticationÂ object if successful.



15. How does Spring Security handle form-based authentication?
Spring Security intercepts the login POST request, authenticates credentials via the AuthenticationManager, and redirects accordingly.



16. How can you configure multiple authentication providers?
By registering multiple AuthenticationProviderÂ beans in the AuthenticationManagerBuilder:
